===============================================================================

Redis Emulator has been installed!

Next steps:

1. Ensure Solid Cache is configured in your Rails application:
   
   # config/environments/production.rb
   config.cache_store = :solid_cache_store

2. Run Solid Cache migrations:
   
   rails solid_cache:install:migrations
   rails db:migrate

3. Use Redis::Emulator in your application:
   
   redis = Redis::Emulator.new
   redis.set("mykey", "myvalue")
   redis.get("mykey") # => "myvalue"

4. You can also configure it globally in config/initializers/redis_emulator.rb

For more information, see the README.md file.

===============================================================================
